         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Kew ¶ May 14 /81. ¶ My dear Baron ¶  ¶ I am in receipt of yours of 5/2/81, asking about the well-being of the  ¶ Livistona ¶   ¶ australis ¶ : ¶  — it is alive &amp; there is every reason to expect that i...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.05.14</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS embossed with crest of Royal Gardens Kew.</p>
               </note>Kew</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">May 14 /81.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am in receipt of yours of 5/2/81, asking about the well-being of the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Livistona</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">australis</hi>
               </seg>:<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">M to J. Hooker, 5 February 1881 (in this edition as 81-02-05a). Hooker had reported the safe arrival of the </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; font-style: italic; ">Livistona</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; "> in J. Hooker to M, 6 October 1880.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> — it is alive &amp; there is every reason to expect that it will continue to live, &amp; eventually become a fine plant — but the evolution of fully formed leaves &amp; of a crown of them will I fear be a very long affair, and will disappoint the nurserymen.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You ask about the results of the many packets of seeds which you have from time to time sent us — these have yielded a large harvest of plants, but as in the case of all tropical countries it is a very small portion that are worth cultivation, &amp; still fewer worth figuring. Many are shrubs that only flower after getting old &amp; then have very inconspicuous flowers. I today saw a pretty little <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Sollya">Sollya</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> (from you) coming into flower, which may I hope be worth figuring.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You ask me to allow you to finish the N. Queensland Flora.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 16 March 1881 and 23 March 1881.</p>
               </note> I only hope that you will do so, I have not the smallest intention of meddling with it &amp; never had. I was not aware that Hill had gone collecting for Kew — but am glad to hear that we may expect some Palms from him.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The red var. of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Correa%20Lawrenciana">Correa Lawrenciana</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> looks well &amp; will doubtless flower: — though I cannot believe it would be hardy with us. No australian or Tasmanian plant is hardy in S. of England: a few as <name key="Eucalyptus%20Gunnii">Eucalyptus Gunnii</name>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">withstand</hi>
               </seg>, or rather <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">exist</hi>
               </seg> under our atrocious climate — but none thrive &amp; no Correa would stand a single winter.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was not aware of the value of <name key="Pilocarpus">Pilocarpus</name> in diptheria.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 23 March 1881.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have received the new Edition of "Select Plants"<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B81.13.10.</p>
               </note> from Sydney, with many thanks</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever sincerly yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jos D Hooker</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Livistona%20australis">Livistona australis</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Sollya">Sollya</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Correa%20Lawrenciana">Correa Lawrenciana</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus%20Gunnii">Eucalyptus Gunnii</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Pilocarpus">Pilocarpus</name>
            </p>
